# Change an account admin or legal representative

This guide helps partner support teams handle requests to change an account administrator (admin) or legal representative — what to collect, what to tell your user, how to track progress, and when to escalate.

For the full technical walkthrough, refer to [Account administrator change](https://docs.swan.io/topics/accounts/memberships/admin-change) on docs.swan.io. For user-facing instructions, share [Change your account's legal representative](https://support.swan.io/hc/en-150/articles/17763494332317) on support.swan.io.

:::info Key takeaways

- Changing an account admin or legal representative **requires a support request**. It can't be done through the API or Dashboard alone.

- Complete documents are the best way to avoid delays. Missing documents move the request back into information collection.

- The secure form link is valid for **7 calendar days** and doesn't save progress.

- The change applies to **all accounts** belonging to the account holder, not just one.

- After the change is completed, Swan doesn't automatically remove or downgrade the previous admin.

:::

## Admin vs. legal representative changes

| Change type | What it means | Applies to |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Change account admin** | Transfer administrative control of the account to a different person. | Company accounts |
| **Change legal representative** | Update who is recognized as the company's legal representative. | Company accounts only: companies, associations, homeowner associations, and other legal entities |

This doesn't apply to individual or self-employed account holders. For full details on account memberships and permissions, refer to [Account memberships](https://docs.swan.io/topics/accounts/memberships/).

## Check if you need a support request

Not every membership change requires a support request:

| Action | Support request needed? | Where to go |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Add a new account member | No | [Add multiple memberships](https://docs.swan.io/topics/accounts/memberships/guide-add-multiple/) |
| Change a member's permissions | No | [Update a membership](https://docs.swan.io/topics/accounts/memberships/guide-update/) |
| Disable a member | No, unless they're the legal representative | [Disable a membership](https://docs.swan.io/topics/accounts/memberships/guide-disable/) |
| Change account admin or legal representative | **Yes** | Follow this guide. |

