## Before you submit the request

Before asking your user to start the change request, gather as much context as possible so Swan can process it without repeated follow-ups:

1. Identify the company and the requested new admin or legal representative.
1. Check whether your user already provided supporting documents.
1. Include all known context and attachments in the first support request.
1. Don't ask your user for information you already have in your own tools — account references, previously attached documents, etc.
1. Ask for missing information in one complete request, not across multiple follow-ups.

:::note
Swan still runs its own compliance checks — this guide covers what you need to do on your side.
:::

## Prepare documents

Missing documents are the primary cause of delays. The exact documents required depend on the company type and situation — Swan determines what's missing after reviewing the request. For the full list, refer to [required supporting documents](https://docs.swan.io/topics/accounts/memberships/admin-change#required-supporting-documents) on docs.swan.io.

### Checklist

Share this with your user before they open the form:

- [ ] Valid identity document for the new legal representative (color, front and back)
- [ ] Official proof of the legal representative change (board resolution, assembly minutes, or updated articles of association)
- [ ] Updated articles of association, if changed
- [ ] Power of attorney, if someone other than the new legal representative completes the form
- [ ] Updated proof of company registration, if registration details changed
- [ ] General assembly minutes, for homeowner associations

