## Request an admin or legal representative change

### Step 1: Your user submits a support request

Your user [submits a request](https://supportform.swan.io/) asking to initiate the change.

The request should include:

- Account holder or company name
- Current admin or legal representative, if known
- New admin or legal representative
- Reason for the change
- Any supporting documents already available

### Step 2: Swan sends a secure form link

Swan creates the change request and sends your user a secure form link. The link is valid for **7 calendar days**.

The form collects:

- Requester details
- New admin or legal representative details
- Reason for the change
- Supporting documents

:::warning
Tell your user to gather all documents **before** opening the link — the form doesn't save progress.
:::

### Step 3: Your user completes the form and uploads documents

Your user fills out the form with the new admin or legal representative's details and uploads the supporting documents.

### Step 4: Swan reviews the submission

Swan reviews everything — the request, the account, and the documents.

If additional documents are needed, Swan sends a **separate upload link**. The original form link won't work for this.

### Step 5: Swan completes the change

What happens next depends on whether the new person is already an account member. Swan handles the invitation, identity verification, and promotion — you don't need to manage these steps. For the full technical detail on what Swan does at this stage, refer to [Account administrator change](https://docs.swan.io/topics/accounts/memberships/admin-change) on docs.swan.io.

Your user can track the request status from the form URL. For a full explanation of each status, refer to [Account administrator change statuses](https://docs.swan.io/topics/accounts/memberships/admin-change#statuses) on docs.swan.io.

:::warning
The change applies to **all accounts** belonging to the account holder, not just one account.
:::

---

## After the change

Swan doesn't automatically remove or downgrade the previous admin. Their membership and permissions stay the same.

After the change is completed, the new admin should review the previous admin's access and decide whether to keep, disable, or downgrade it.

## Fix common issues

### The form link expired

The form link expires after **7 calendar days** and doesn't save progress. Your user must [submit a new request](https://supportform.swan.io/) for a new link. There's no way to recover what was entered.

### Your user can't submit the form

Ask your user for a screenshot of the issue, then contact Swan Support with the screenshot and request context.

### Swan requested additional documents but your user doesn't understand what's needed

Swan sends document requests directly to the user at the email address registered on the account, with a **separate upload link**.

Common missing items:

- Proof of the legal representative change (board resolution or general assembly minutes)
- Power of attorney (when someone other than the new legal representative completes the form)
- Updated articles of association
- Supporting identity document

Ask your user to forward the email so you can help them figure out what's needed.

### Your user submitted the form but hasn't heard back

1. Confirm the user actually completed and submitted the form — not just opened it.
1. Check spam and junk folders for emails from Swan.
1. If confirmed, contact Swan Support with the account holder details and submission date.

### The legal representative is no longer part of the entity

This is common for homeowner associations and companies where the previous legal representative has left:

1. Gather documentation proving the departure (resignation letter, updated company registry, or general assembly minutes appointing a new representative).
1. Have the new legal representative or an authorized person [submit a support request](https://supportform.swan.io/).
1. Include the departure documentation along with the standard required documents.
1. If the outgoing representative is unreachable and their identity document isn't available, note this in the support request. Swan's verification team will advise on alternative documentation.

### The new person's membership is blocked

If the new admin or legal representative's membership is blocked, Swan can't complete the change until the blocker is resolved. Contact Swan Support — don't attempt workarounds.

